==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: adulterating
<hw>adulterating</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>making impure or
corrupt by virtue of extraneous origin; -- of impurities.</def>
<illu>the <ex>adulterating</ex> effect of extraneous materials</illu>
<ant>purifying</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adulterant</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>making impure or corrupt by adding extraneous
materials; -- of people.</def> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adulterant.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulteration</ent>⟦br⟧
